        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add opt-in billing guard probes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR changes the cron billing safety behavior from an unconditional stop into an opt-in billing guard for recurring `agentTurn` cron jobs.\n\nDefault behavior is unchanged. Unless `cron.billingGuard.enabled` is explicitly set, recurring jobs continue to use the existing retry/backoff behavior.\n\nWhen the guard is enabled and a recurring `agentTurn` run records `lastErrorReason === \"billing\"`, the scheduler now:\n\n- keeps the job enabled;\n- schedules the next run using the billing guard probe backoff;\n- logs a warning that a billing guard probe was scheduled;\n- returns to the normal recurring schedule automatically after a successful run.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nRecurring scheduled agent jobs can repeatedly retry after provider-side billing failures. Billing failures are usually not fixed by immediately retrying the same request, but permanently disabling the job after a single error is too aggressive for existing users.\n\nThis PR avoids both failure modes:\n\n- no default compatibility break for existing recurring cron jobs;\n- opt-in deployments can slow billing-classified retries into probe cadence and recover automatically when billing/provider access is fixed.\n\n## Behavior\n\nWithout opt-in:\n\n```text\nrecurring agentTurn cron + billing-classified error\n=> existing recurring retry/backoff behavior is preserved\n```\n\nWith opt-in:\n\n```json5\n{\n  cron: {\n    billingGuard: {\n      enabled: true,\n      probeBackoffMs: [1800000, 3600000, 7200000]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n```text\nrecurring agentTurn cron + billing-classified error\n=> enabled remains true\n=> nextRunAtMs is delayed by billingGuard.probeBackoffMs\n=> a later successful run clears lastErrorReason and consecutiveErrors\n=> normal recurring schedule resumes\n```\n\nThe guard only applies to recurring `agentTurn` jobs and only when the error is classified as `billing`. Rate-limit-only failures keep the existing retry/backoff path.\n\n## Evidence\n\nValidation performed on this branch:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cron/service/timer.billing-safety.test.ts src/cron/service/timer.regression.test.ts\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests       68 passed (68)\n```\n\nAdditional validation:\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nResult: no whitespace/check errors.\n\nFocused coverage now verifies:\n\n- default billing behavior is preserved when the guard is not enabled;\n- opt-in billing guard schedules a probe without disabling the recurring job;\n- rate-limit-only failures keep the existing retry/backoff behavior;\n- successful billing guard probes recover automatically and return the job to the normal recurring schedule.\n\n## Why This Replaces The Previous Approach\n\nThe earlier version disabled recurring `agentTurn` jobs after one billing-classified failure. That avoided repeated requests, but it changed the default recurring cron contract and required manual operator recovery after billing was fixed.\n\nThis version keeps the default contract compatible and makes the safer behavior explicit opt-in with automatic recovery.\n\n## Scope\n\nChanged files:\n\n- `src/config/types.cron.ts`\n- `src/cron/service/timer.ts`\n- `src/cron/service/timer.billing-safety.test.ts`\n- `docs/automation/cron-jobs.md`\n- `docs/cli/cron.md`\n",
        "branch": "pr/cron-billing-safety",
